      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">Vignetted head and shoulder shot of a woman wearing a dark urban dress and earrings.</ab>
      <ab subtype="comment" type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">Ekaterina Hadzhi Decheva, wife of Captain Rayco Nikolov. At the time she was a widow. Captain Rayco Nikolov (1840 - 1885) was a volunteer in the Serbo-Ottoman War of 1878, and an officer in the Bulgarian voluntary army units during the Russo-Ottoman War of 1877-1878. He took an active part in preparing the 1885 unification of the Principality of Bulgaria and the, at the time, Ottoman province of Eastern Rumelia.</ab>
